This document specify the new data plane design in video session processing.
The new design attempts to unify all existing stream processing modes
(SPTS muxing, passthru, MPTS remuxing) into a unified scheme.

A video stream data structure has the following facilities:
  - flags: PID_REMAP, PROCESS_TIME, PROCESS_PSI, PASSTHRU
    - PID_REMAP
      - whether to remap pids
      - whether to include ES pids in pid_table
    - PROCESS_TIME
      - whether to perform dejittering and clock recovery
    - PROCESS_PSI
      - whether to snoop for PAT/PMT
    - PASSTHRU
      - whether to passthru any PIDs not in pid table
      - PIDs passthru here will not be covered by pid collision / cc error
        detection
  - number of programs allocated (SPTS/MPTS support)
  - blocked pid list (post FCS)
  - passthru pid list (post FCS)
  - pid table:
    - flags (used, PAT, PMT, video, drop, passthru)
    - pid_idx (for remapping purpose)
    - prev CC (for CC error checking)
    - contains PAT, PMTs, and pids on blocked pid and passthru pid lists
      (with flags appropriately set)
    - contains ESs in PMTs for PID_REMAP sessions
    - CC error detection apply only to pids in pid table
  - program list (to hold PSI sections, for PSI processing)


On each QAM:
  - pid usage map (for pid allocation, and collision detection)
  - prognum usage map (for program number allocation, and collision detection)
  - pid/program number collision applies on pids in PAT/PMT,
    and pids in passthru pid list.

----------------------------

VOD/SDV sessions:
  - PID_REMAP, PROCESS_TIME, PROCESS_PSI
  - number of programs = 1
  - pid_table contains PAT, PMT and ES pids

Passthru sessions:
  - PROCESS_TIME, PROCESS_PSI, PASSTHRU
  - number of progams = max programs expected
  - pid_table contains PAT and PMT PIDs only
  - CC error detection supported on PAT/PMT pids only.
  - program number collision detection supported
  - pid collision applies on PIDs in PAT/PMTs.
  - ghost pid passthru supported (without pid collision / CC error detection)

Data injection sessions:
  - PASSTHRU
  - number of programs = 0
  - pid_table not used
  - all pids are passthru (except for PAT and NULL)
  - no pid collision / CC error detection

----------------------------

PID/program filtering support:
  - default is to forward all PMT pids (and corresponding program) in PAT,
    and all ES pids in PMTs
  - to drop a program, add the PMT pid to the blocked pid list
    (Note: ALL programs on the PMT pid will be dropped!)
  - to drop an ES, add the ES pid to the blocked pid list
    (Note: PMT regeneration will need to consider this!)
  - PID dropping is supported using the pid table,
    with corresponding drop flag set

PID insertion support:
  - default is to drop all pids not referenced in PAT/PMT
  - dropped pids will not be CC checked
  - to forward an unreferenced pid, add it to the passthru pid list
  - pids on passthru pid list will be forwarded to ALL output sessions
    without remapping

Basic operation:
  - will always snoop PAT for PMT pids
  - will always regenerate PAT

PID remapping:
  - when on:
    - the program numbers, PMT pids, and ES pids will be remapped
    - PMT will be regenerated
    - only pids in pid table with drop_flag not set is forwarded to output
      (includes PMT & ES pids, and user specified passthru pids)
  - when off:
    - all program numbers, PMT pids, and ES pids will be preserved
    - PMT will be passthru
    - at session start or during PSI change, will detect program number/pid
      collision and block the session if necessary

CLI:
  - SPTS muxing: video udp <dst_udp> program <prog_num>
  - MPTS passthru: video udp <dst_udp> passthru
  - MPTS remuxing: video udp <dst_udp> program <start_prog_num> <last_prog_num>


========================================================================

Try another flag scheme:

PROCESS_PSI:
  - first place PAT in pid_table to snoop PAT
  - snoop PAT to discover PMTs, put them in pid_table for lookup
  - output PAT will include PMTs found in this session
  - input PAT will always be dropped, regardless of this setting

PROCESS_PMT:
  - snoop PMT to discover ESs, put them in pid_table for lookup

REMAP:
  - will remap program number, PMT pids, and ES pids

PASSTHRU:
  - for input PIDs not found in pid table, this indicates whether
    to passthru or drop

--------------------------------------

For VOD/SDV:
  PROCESS_PAT, PROCESS_PMT, REMAP, PROCESS_TIME

For dirty MPTS passthru:
  PROCESS_PAT, PROCESS_PMT

For MPTS passthru with CC checking:
  PROCESS_PAT, PROCESS_PMT, PROCESS_TIME

For data injection:
  PASSTHRU (will drop input PAT)


========================================================================

Operation:

If PROCESS_PSI set:
- put PAT in pid_table
- snoop PAT:
  - check for prog_num and pid collision
  - update qam usage map for prog_num and PMT pids
  - generate in_prog for each input program
  - put PMT pids in pid_table
- snoop PMT:
  - check for ES pid collision
  - update qam usage map for ES pids
  - update in_prog for PMT
  - if PID_REMAP, put ES pids in pid_table


Input TP processing:
- if NULL PID, drop it
- PID lookup
- if not found, passthru or drop it based on PASSTHRU
- if PAT, process PAT
- if PMT, process PMT
- other ES processing


Output TP processing:
- if PAT, update PAT
- if PMT, update PMT
- if drop_flag, drop TP
- other ES processing


Output PAT processing:
- if new PAT:
  - remove prog list, clean up usage map
  - clean up pid_table
